20.google.com/">Aloud</a>的人工智能配音服务，该服务是由谷歌 Area 120 孵化器开发的。该工具将消除通常方式（人工翻译和旁白）配音所需的时间和巨额费用，从而使创作者能够接触到更广泛的全球受众。</p><p> Aloud 承诺使用人工智能“在几分钟内完成高质量配音”。该工具首先创建一个基于文本的翻译，创作者可以检查和编辑，然后生成配音。用户可以选择不同的叙述者、发布方式等。最重要的是，该服务“免费”，Aloud 的网站称。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><div id="1015327e76f4450aae6960d4c6017dcd"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/RQbKv2bhY_s?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><p> YouTube 产品管理副总裁 Amjad Hanif 告诉<em>The Verge</em> ，YouTube 目前正在与“数百名”创作者一起测试该工具。据 Aloud 称，它目前提供英语版本，并允许您用西班牙语和葡萄牙语配音，“即将推出更多语言”。</p><p>从用户的角度来看，该设置在齿轮图标中显示为“音轨”切换，位于字幕下方。 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:YouTube;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=89f68c82-f255-44fa-8db9-03fec996b93a&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=YouTube&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI4OWY2OGM4Mi1mMjU1LTQ0ZmEtOGRiOS0wM2ZlYzk5NmI5M2EiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cueW91dHViZS5jb20vd2F0Y2g_dj04Y2tnRDQwQ0o2SSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiYmFkY2IwOTYtNmMyNS00N2YwLWE1ZGYtM2UzYmNhMTA3NTQ0In0&amp;signature=AQAAASWW4vTRRefUXsjSYRxInBQRnNTJ3pXG2p1JvsQowUVh&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D8ckgD40CJ6I">阿米巴姐妹科学频道预告片</a>就是一个例子，它使用英语作为母语，并有由 Aloud 的人工智能创建的西班牙语选项。</p><p>谷歌在其主题演讲中表示，轻松为语言配音的能力可以扩大创作者的影响力，而无需做任何其他事情。目前还没有提及 Aloud 的配音工具何时会得到更广泛的使用。不过，哈尼夫表示，在未来，YouTube 将“使翻译后的音轨听起来像创作者的声音，并具有更多的表情和口型同步”。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/youtubes-new-tool-can-automatically-dub-videos-into-other-languages-093624288.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/youtubes-new-tool-can-automatically-dub-videos-into-other-languages-093624288.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> badcb096-6c25-47f0-a5df-3e3bca107544</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2023 09:36:24 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687517856</ingested><modified> 2023-06-23T10:57:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="2362" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-08/45c46cf0-260b-11ed-9bf9-3bb387a3204a" width="3543"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2362" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-08/45c46cf0-260b-11ed-9bf9-3bb387a3204a" width="3543"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NurPhoto via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[YouTube logo displayed on a phone and headphones are seen in this illustration photo taken in Krakow, Poland on August 22, 2022. (Photo by Jakub Porzycki/NurPhoto via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Music And Audiobook Subscription Services Photo Illustrations]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[US calls upon volunteer experts to help address generative AI risks]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>美国政府正在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.nist.gov/news-events/news/2023/06/biden-harris-administration-announces-new-nist-public-working-group-ai">寻求</a>合格公众的帮助，以了解如何抓住机遇并克服与生成人工智能相关的挑战。美国商务部长吉娜·雷蒙多宣布，美国国家标准与技术研究院 (NIST) 正在成立一个人工智能技术公共工作组，该技术可以生成文本、图像、视频、音乐和代码等内容。该小组还将帮助该机构制定组织可以遵循的关键指南，以应对生成人工智能技术带来的风险。</p><p>据该机构称，该小组将由来自私营和公共部门的具有技术专长的志愿者组成，并将通过在线协作工作空间进行合作。首先，该小组将收集关于如何使用 NIST 人工智能风险管理框架（该机构开发的框架，旨在“更好地管理与人工智能相关的个人、组织和社会的风险”）的意见，以支持生成人工智能的发展技术。然后，该小组预计将支持该机构的人工智能相关测试和评估。然而，其长期目标是探索如何利用生成人工智能来解决我们这个时代最紧迫的问题，例如与健康、气候变化和整个环境有关的问题。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>雷蒙多在一份声明中表示：</p><p> “拜登总统已经明确表示，我们必须努力利用人工智能的巨大潜力，同时管理人工智能对我们的经济、国家安全和社会构成的风险。最近发布的 NIST 人工智能风险管理框架可以帮助最大限度地减少生成人工智能技术造成的潜在危害在此框架的基础上，这个新的公共工作组将帮助为那些正在开发、部署和使用生成式人工智能并有责任确保其可信度的组织提供必要的指导。”</p><p>政府一直在努力跟上生成人工智能技术快速发展的步伐。今年四月，国家电信和信息管理局就追究人工智能创造者责任的可能法规<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/biden-administration-wants-your-input-on-rules-for-ai-models-like-chatgpt-193527890.html">征求公众意见</a>。白宫还<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-white-house-is-examining-how-companies-use-ai-to-monitor-workers-174217114.html">邀请</a>美国工人分享如何在工作场所使用自动化工具。然后在 6 月，众议员特德·刘（D-CA）和肯·巴克（Ken Buck）（共和党）提出立法，将设立一个 20 人委员会，研究如何“减轻人工智能的风险和可能的危害”，同时“保护”美国的全球科技强国的地位。这项立法是在微软副主席兼总裁布拉德·史密斯在华盛顿特区发表讲话并<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-appeals-for-a-new-us-agency-to-regulate-ai-095510698.html">呼吁</a>美国联邦政府建立一个专注于监管人工智能的新机构之后出台的。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/us-calls-upon-volunteer-experts-to-help-address-generative-ai-risks-063956572.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/us-calls-upon-volunteer-experts-to-help-address-generative-ai-risks-063956572.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 73d01f36-5ea7-4e38-a8b6-dbe50d9b0b22</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 23 Jun 2023 06:39:56 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687502397</ingested><modified> 2023-06-23T06:40:07+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/65fb1e30-1186-11ee-bfd7-8e808cf80e65" width="7000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/65fb1e30-1186-11ee-bfd7-8e808cf80e65" width="7000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[BlackJack3D via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[AI concept. 3D render]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Digital Mind. Brain Artificial Intelligence Concept]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[E3 2024 and 2025 aren't canceled (yet)]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>自 2019 年以来，电子娱乐博览会就没有再举办过现场活动。现在，它可能不会在 2024 年或 2025 年回归——至少不会在洛杉矶会议中心举行。根据<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.resetera.com/threads/e3-2024-and-e3-2025-have-been-cancelled.733938/">ResetEra 上分享的</a><a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://tourism.lacity.gov/sites/g/files/wph1946/files/2023-06/06-21-23%20CTD%20Commission%20Meeting%20Packet.pdf">洛杉矶市旅游委员会</a>规划文件，视频游戏贸易展已取消未来两年的现场活动。该文件的大会销售数据特别指出，其数据“包括 2024 年和 2025 年 E3 取消”。</p><p>尽管该市文件表明 E3 2024 不会在洛杉矶会议中心举办，但电子软件协会本身似乎对确认整个活动被取消犹豫不决。 “ESA 目前正在与 ESA 成员和其他利益相关者就 E3 2024（及以后）进行对话，”该组织告诉 Engadget。 “目前尚未就这些事件做出最终决定。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>目前尚不清楚这对 E3 本身意味着什么。尽管自 COVID-19 大流行导致 E3 2020 取消以来，电子软件协会尚未举办过现场交易，但该组织确实在 2021 年举办了一场<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/e3-2021-closed-captions-fail-224552954.html">纯数字活动。</a> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/e3-2022-fully-canceled-194216531.html">该展会的现场版本和数字版本都没有</a>回归2022年。</p><p>当该展会<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/e3-2023-has-been-canceled-211201976.html">在 2023 年再次取消</a>时，ESA 总裁兼首席执行官 Stanley Pierre-Louis 告诉 GamesIndustry，贸易展可能需要改变才能生存。 “E3 将进行迭代，以确保满足想要在这个全球平台上进行营销的公司的需求。”皮埃尔-路易斯说道。 “这意味着它将迭代人们与 E3 的互动方式。我们希望满足那些将其视为重要平台并且会随着时间的推移而不断发展的玩家的需求。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/e3-2024-and-2025-arent-canceled-yet-222141813.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/e3-2024-and-2025-arent-canceled-yet-222141813.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> f638e064-10a7-479b-85e9-aa2f70e0b55d</guid><dc:creator>肖恩·巴克利</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 22 Jun 2023 22:21:41 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687472493</ingested><modified> 2023-06-22T22:21:36+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sean Buckley]]></category><media:content height="2592" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/e56e28f0-cf3d-11ed-bdbf-6bbeaf478dd8" width="3888"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2592" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-03/e56e28f0-cf3d-11ed-bdbf-6bbeaf478dd8" width="3888"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[AP Images for T-Mobile]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Atmosphere outside of the Los Angeles Convention Center before the T-Mobile G2x Arcade Diner at the Electronic Entertainment Expo (E3) convention on Tuesday, June 7, 2011 in Los Angeles. (Shea Walsh / AP Images for T-Mobile)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[E3 T-Mobile G2x Arcade Diner]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pocono Raceway’s ‘jet drier’ credited with keeping I-95’s reopening on time]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>周末下雨，费城 95 号州际公路倒塌路段的重新开放可能会被推迟。但<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://billypenn.com/2023/06/22/i95-rebuild-jet-dryer-nascar-pocono-raceway/">据</a><em>比利佩恩</em>称，官员们呼叫了增援：从附近的赛道调来了一台巨型喷气式烘干机。正如宾夕法尼亚州州长乔什·夏皮罗所承诺的那样，干燥机预计将确保高速公路在本周末开放。</p><p>喷射干燥机用于防止附近波科诺赛道湿滑，由一个改装的直升机涡轮机组成，安装在雪佛兰索罗德的后面。宾夕法尼亚州交通部长迈克·卡罗尔（Mike Carroll）在该地区任职时曾与赛马场官员共事，他知道当暴风雨天气可能会推迟重新开放时该给谁打电话。 “我们认识卡罗尔先生很多年了，他是宾夕法尼亚州东北部的代表，”波科诺赛道高级营销总监 Ricky Durst 说。 “他非常了解赛道，知道我们在比赛期间经常不得不应对天气情况，并且知道我们有能力和工具来干燥沥青。”据报道，赛道上还带来了一辆雪佛兰科迈罗配速车，但其在沥青干燥过程中的用途尚不清楚。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>昨晚，工人们在计划的周末重新开放之前铺设了六车道路段，重新连接倒塌路段周围的高速公路。喷射干燥机的到来对夏皮罗来说应该是一个受欢迎的消息，他昨天表示，“我现在可以自信地说，本周末 95 号州际公路上的交通将畅通无阻……我们已经安全、顺利地完成了该项目的每个阶段提前于计划。” <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://news.yahoo.com/huge-hassle-95-collapse-snarls-163557322.html">上周末，立交桥的一部分倒塌</a>，一辆油罐车在下面爆炸，起火，导致司机死亡，并导致整个工作周的交通瘫痪。</p><p>与此同时，Twitch 主播布伦特·斯库利 (Brent Schooley) 看到了一个有趣的机会，因为当地居民正在关注 I-95 州际公路的重建进展。这位位于费城的软件开发商开始直播<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.twitch.tv/fixthatjawn">该作品的现场直播</a>，并伴有 LoFi 节拍。斯库利<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.inquirer.com/news/pennsylvania/i95-livestream-feed-twitch-rebuild-philadelphia-20230621.html">告诉</a><em>《费城问询报》</em> ，他开始了他的“修复下颌！”计划。当人们检查进展时，流提供了一个急需的“模因聊天室”。尽管有些人猜测这是州长公关团队明智的青年推广举措，但该项目是自然而然地产生的。夏皮罗州长的新闻秘书曼努埃尔·邦德 (Manuel Bonder) 表示：“这是这一切真正走向灭亡的又一个例子。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/pocono-raceways-jet-drier-credited-with-keeping-i-95s-reopening-on-time-211512444.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/pocono-raceways-jet-drier-credited-with-keeping-i-95s-reopening-on-time-211512444.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 9de428e0-2b32-48b5-bfb2-2d3691438833</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 22 Jun 2023 21:15:12 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687466182</ingested><modified> 2023-06-22T20:36:26+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="1536" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/c8689810-1139-11ee-bffe-32f3eb0220c0" width="2560"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1536" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/c8689810-1139-11ee-bffe-32f3eb0220c0" width="2560"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Ricky Durst / BillyPenn]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A red Chevy Silverado with a modified helicopter turbine attached to its back.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Pocono Raceway jet dryer]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[New Indiana Jones game became an Xbox exclusive after Microsoft bought ZeniMax]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>众所周知，微软收购 ZeniMax 必然会<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-bethesda-zenimax-game-pass-200652624.html">影响跨平台版本</a>，但现在有迹象表明游戏玩家可能会错过一些主要版本。在联邦贸易委员会 (FTC) 律师寻求<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-activision-blizzard-merger-temporarily-blocked-by-us-judge-061933491.html">针对微软与动视暴雪交易的禁令</a>的询问下，Bethesda 副总裁 Pete Hines<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/stephentotilo/status/1671939745293688832">透露</a>，迪士尼与 ZeniMax 达成协议，将在多个游戏机上发行<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/bethesda-machinegames-indiana-jones-game-164516126.html">MachineGames 的《夺宝奇兵》游戏</a>。然而，在微软收购 ZeniMax 后，交易进行了修改，使其成为 Xbox 主机的独占产品。</p><p> FTC 还<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/stephentotilo/status/1671875372634324993">认为</a>，贝塞斯达的科幻史诗<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/starfield-has-been-delayed-to-september-6th-161635848.html"><em>《Starfield》</em></a>在被微软收购之前就已登陆 PlayStation 5。<em>彭博社</em>此前<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-06-01/arcane-s-redfall-misfire-for-xbox-panned-after-7-5-billion-microsoft-deal?sref=10lNAhZ9#xj4y7vzkg">报道</a>称，贝塞斯达砍掉了<em>《Redfall》</em>的 PlayStation 版本，不过考虑到这款吸血鬼射击游戏的<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-was-reportedly-hands-off-with-xbox-dud-redfall-201436340.html">反响不佳，</a>这并不令人担忧。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>海因斯<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.ign.com/articles/machinegames-indiana-jones-game-was-originally-planned-for-release-on-ps5">声称，由于迪士尼许可的性质，《夺宝奇兵》获得独家授权</a>。这位贝塞斯达高管表示，迪士尼在该项目上收到了“大量反馈”，这限制了开发时间，而 Xbox 独占将使游戏保持在正轨上，同时提供“一定程度的清晰度”。 <em>Starfield</em>和<em>Redfall</em>等游戏都是原创游戏。</p><p>我们已要求贝塞斯达发表评论。 2021 年，Xbox 首席执行官 Phil Spencer 表示，微软对 ZeniMax 的控制将带来“出色的独家游戏”。由于合同义务，当时仍在开发中的一些游戏，例如<em>《死亡循环》</em>和<em>《幽灵线：东京》</em> ，仍将登陆 PlayStation。</p><p>这些披露并不一定会巩固联邦贸易委员会<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ftc-microsoft-activision-blizzard-antitrust-competition-lawsuit-191341476.html">阻止微软收购</a>动视暴雪的努力。然而，它们看起来并不好——它们表明一些玩家正在失去以前注定要在他们选择的游戏机上玩的备受瞩目的游戏。微软已承诺未来几年<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-makes-its-10-year-call-of-duty-pact-with-nintendo-official-091655095.html">将在多个平台上发布《使命召唤》</a> ，以争取监管部门的批准，但如果官员们仍然担心其他独家游戏，这可能无济于事。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/new-indiana-jones-game-became-an-xbox-exclusive-after-microsoft-bought-zenimax-210157957.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/new-indiana-jones-game-became-an-xbox-exclusive-after-microsoft-bought-zenimax-210157957.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 86690bcc-1e4e-4727-a5bb-5884312b7ae6</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 22 Jun 2023 21:01:57 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687468471</ingested><modified> 2023-06-22T21:14:35+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Game Consoles]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="3599" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/cced8820-1132-11ee-97db-ec5e0d3dca83" width="5399"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3599" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/cced8820-1132-11ee-97db-ec5e0d3dca83" width="5399"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Yara Nardi / reuters]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The 76th Cannes Film Festival - Cannes, France, May 15, 2023. People walk past a giant poster for the film "Indiana Jones and the Dial of Destiny" (Indiana Jones et le cadran de la destinee) in front of the Carlton Cannes hotel on the Croisette waterfront promenade, on the eve of the opening ceremony. REUTERS/Yara Nardi]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[FILMFESTIVAL-CANNES/]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta pulls news content from Canadian Facebook and Instagram]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>本月初，Facebook 的母公司 Meta 通过博客文章宣布，如果政府通过拟议的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.parl.ca/legisinfo/en/bill/44-1/c-18">《在线新闻法案》</a> ， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/meta-test-will-limit-news-posts-for-facebook-and-instagram-users-in-canada-104026273.html">它将取消加拿大 FB 和 Instagram 上所有新闻内容的可用性</a>。周四，加拿大议会就这么做了，几小时后，Meta 证实它将兑现其威胁。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://about.fb.com/news/2023/06/changes-to-news-availability-on-our-platforms-in-canada/">该公司发布消息</a>称：“今天，我们确认，在《在线新闻法案》（Bill C-18）生效之前，加拿大所有用户将停止在 Facebook 和 Instagram 上获取新闻。” “我们一再表示，为了遵守今天在议会通过的 C-18 法案，来自新闻媒体（包括新闻出版商和广播公司）的内容将不再向访问我们加拿大平台的人提供。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> 《在线新闻法案》 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Globe and Mail;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=a25615a6-d7c2-433c-8dc1-01b732da27f0&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Globe+and+Mail&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAXvUX2x1B15tfU1EmKgQsW6_f3aNH7RcHwQCnFAJ_0WH&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fpolitics%2Farticle-bill-c18-online-news-law-explained%2F">旨在解决</a>过去二十年来加拿大新闻机构广告收入急剧下降的问题。为此，它要求谷歌和 Meta 等大型科技公司与这些媒体协商在各自平台上播放上述报道的报销计划。</p><p> 6 月初，Meta 宣布正在致力于为其 C-18 问题开发基于软件的解决方案。截至周四，这些努力仍在继续，“目前影响了加拿大的一小部分用户”。除了失去新闻功能外，Meta 向用户保证 Facebook 体验的其他方面不会受到影响。</p><p>这并不是 Meta 第一次因政府监管而拿起玩具回家。 In 2021, the company <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/facebook-australia-news-links-blocked-185149753.html">removed its news features from the Australian market</a> after the country passed similar compensation legislation — even going so far as to prevent publishers from linking to their posts on the social media platform. That move negatively impacted the pages of multiple Australian government agencies as well as <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/facebook-australia-news-ban-took-down-government-pages-045625746.html">numerous nonprofit organizations from the region</a> before being reversed.</p><p> &quot;This legislation sets a precedent where the government decides who enters into these news content agreements, and ultimately, how much the party that already receives value from the free service gets paid,&quot; William Easton, Facebook&#39;s managing director for Australia and New Zealand, wrote in a blog post at the time. &quot;We will now prioritize investments to other countries, as part of our plans to invest in new licensing news programs and experiences.&quot;</p><p> Google, which would also be affected by the bill&#39;s implementation, has not yet announced any plans to officially cut service in the nation. It did begin testing <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/google-tests-blocking-news-content-some-canadians-2023-02-23/">a means of blocking news access in Canada</a> in February.</p><p> Google spokesperson Jenn Crider told Engadget:</p><p> &quot;We&#39;re doing everything we can to avoid an outcome that no-one wants. Every step of the way, we&#39;ve proposed thoughtful and pragmatic solutions that would have improved the Bill and cleared the path for us to increase our already significant investments in the Canadian news ecosystem. So far, none of our concerns have been addressed. Bill C-18 is about to become law and remains unworkable. We are continuing to urgently seek to work with the government on a path forward.&quot;</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/meta-pulls-news-content-from-canadian-facebook-and-instagram-204431447.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/meta-pulls-news-content-from-canadian-facebook-and-instagram-204431447.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1c98d3d3-e0ea-4f24-a18d-e5802aa98229</guid><dc:creator> Andrew Tarantola</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 22 Jun 2023 20:44:31 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687492272</ingested><modified> 2023-06-23T03:51:17+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Andrew Tarantola]]></category><media:content height="2103" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/d9abd0d0-113c-11ee-bccb-76fe0c8a493b" width="3154"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2103" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/d9abd0d0-113c-11ee-bccb-76fe0c8a493b" width="3154"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NurPhoto via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[An image of a woman holding a cell phone in front of a 